South African Daybook: Credit Demand Climbs, Budget Data, Avusa, Capitec

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-03-30T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/south-africa-daybook-credit-demand-climbs-budget-data-avusa.html
South African credit demand rose
5.2 percent in February, up from 5.01 percent the previous
month, according to the median estimate of 11 analysts surveyed
by Bloomberg.  The broad M3 measure of  money supply  increased an annual
8.6 percent last month from 8.19 percent in January, according
to the median of nine estimates.  The  Reserve Bank  releases the data at 8 a.m. South African
time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alastair Reed in Johannesburg at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at   vwessels@bloomberg.net  